ast.value: # Auxiliary lemmas for proving that two int numerals are differen
1. Lemmas for reducing the problem to the case where the numerals are positive
2. Lemmas for proving that positive int numerals are nonneg and positive

4. Aux lemmas for pushing nat_abs inside numerals
   nat_abs_zero and nat_abs_one are defined at init/data/int/basic.lean

nat_abs_add_nonneg : ∀ {a b : ℤ}, 0 ≤ a → 0 ≤ b → (a + b).nat_abs = a.nat_abs + b.nat_abs,
n m : ℕ,
h₁ : 0 ≤ of_nat n,
h₂ : 0 ≤ of_nat m,
this : of_nat n + of_nat m = of_nat (n + m)
⊢ (of_nat n + of_nat m).nat_abs = (of_nat n).nat_abs + (of_nat m).nat_abs
no goals

h₂ : -[1+ m] < 0,
this : -[1+ n] + -[1+ m] = -[1+ (n + m).succ]
⊢ (-[1+ n] + -[1+ m]).nat_abs = -[1+ n].nat_abs + -[1+ m].nat_abs
